d and additional startup costs may also come into play that are not charged by Vinehurst. Learn more by calling our office.</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2>Q: Will The Current Owners Offer Training after I purchase?</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div>\r\n<h4>A: In most cases, absolutely. It depends on both You and the Sellers comfort level after the closing of the deal. Typically, that is something that is negotiated directly between You and the Seller.</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2>Q: How Do I Know That The Profit Figures That The Sellers Claim Are True?</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div>\r\n<h4>A: As part of the acquisition process, you will have to go through “due diligence.” During this period the seller is required to present documents to verify his profit numbers. We highly recommend you retain an Accountant to verify all financials provided to you during the DD process.</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h2>Q: How Much Money Will It Take To Buy A Small Business?</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div>\r\n<h4>A: At Vinehurst, our average transaction size is $10million. However, we fully understand many of our Buying clients do not have this type of budget. Contact us today and lets discuss your budget options.</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Buyer FAQS','','publish','closed','closed','','buyer-faqs','','','2016-06-23 13:12:53','2016-06-23 13:12:53','',0,'http://dev.vinehurst.com/?page_id=1088',0,'page','',0),(1139,1,'2016-06-22 12:24:34','2016-06-22 12:24:34',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','1139','','','2016-06-23 13:30:23','2016-06-23 13:30:23','',0,'http://dev.vinehurst.com/?p=1139',10,'nav_menu_item','',0),(1138,1,'2016-06-22 12:24:34','2016-06-22 12:24:34','','What\'s Your Business Worth?','','publish','closed','closed','','1138','','','2016-06-23 13:30:23','2016-06-23 13:30:23','',0,'http://dev.vinehurst.com/?p=1138',11,'nav_menu_item','',0),(1166,1,'2016-06-22 23:30:33','2016-06-22 23:30:33','<h2>Buyer FAQs.</h2>\r\n<h2></h2>\r\n<h2>Q: Do I need A Lawyer and an Accountant to Buy A Business?</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div>\r\n<h4>A: Buying or selling a business can be a complicated venture. While some businesses are sold without the help of accountants and attorneys, we strongly recommend that both the buyer and seller engage professionals.</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h2>Q: Where Can I Go To Look At What Businesses Are Available To Buy?</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div>\r\n<h4>A: Please visit Vinehurst.com to see what is currently available for acquisition.</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2>Q: What Will The Process Of Buying A Company Cost Me?</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div>\r\n<h4>A: At Vinehurst, we have several convenient compensation options for our Buyer clients. Legal and accounting fees are generally required and additional startup costs may also come into play that are not charged by Vinehurst. Learn more by calling our office.</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2>Q: Will The Current Owners Offer Training after I purchase?</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div>\r\n<h4>A: In most cases, absolutely. It depends on both You and the Sellers comfort level after the closing of the deal. Typically, that is something that is negotiated directly between You and the Seller.</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2>Q: How Do I Know That The Profit Figures That The Sellers Claim Are True?</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div>\r\n<h4>A: As part of the acquisition process, you will have to go through “due diligence.” During this period the seller is required to present documents to verify his profit numbers. We highly recommend you retain an Accountant to verify all financials provided to you during the DD process.</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h2>Q: How Much Money Will It Take To Buy A Small Business?</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div>\r\n<h4>A: At Vinehurst, our average transaction size is $10million. However, we fully understand many of our Buying clients do not have this type of budget. Contact us today and lets discuss your budget options.</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Buyer FAQS','','inherit','closed','closed','','1088-revision-v1','','','2016-06-22 23:30:33','2016-06-22 23:30:33','',1088,'http://dev.vinehurst.com/2016/06/22/1088-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1092,1,'2016-06-22 01:13:41','2016-06-22 01:13:41','<h2>Q: Do I Need An Attorney And An Accountant To Buy A Business?</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div id=\"accordion-1\" class=\"accordion-section-content\">\r\n<h4>A: Buying or selling a business can be a complicated venture. While some businesses are sold without the help of accountants and attorneys, we strongly recommend that both the buyer and seller engage professionals.</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2>Q: I\'m A Resident Of Another Country Interested In Obtaining An E-2 Visa, Can You Help?</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div id=\"accordion-2\" class=\"accordion-section-content open\">\r\n<h4>A: While the e-2 process is quite complex and we certainly recommend a consultant that specializes in obtaining visas, several of Transworld\'s agents have done numerous E-2 transactions and can provide enough help to move you along the process.</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"accordion-1\" class=\"accordion-section-content\">\r\n<h2>Q: Where Can I Go To Look At What Businesses Are Available To Buy?</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div id=\"accordion-3\" class=\"accordion-section-content open\">\r\n<h4>A: Our website, www.tworld.com has a search page where you can look at over 4000 businesses.</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2>Q: What Will The Process Of Buying A Company Cost Me?</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div id=\"accordion-4\" class=\"accordion-section-content open\">\r\n<h4>A: Transworld is generally paid by the seller not the buyer. However, other costs do come into play. Legal and accounting fees are generally required and additional startup costs may also come into play.</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2>Q: Will The Current Owners Train Me To Run The Company?</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div id=\"accordion-5\" class=\"accordion-section-content open\">\r\n<h4>A: Depending on the complexities of the business, the former owner will offer varying levels of training. On most small businesses, the owner will offer training for two to four weeks at no cost to the new owner.</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2>Q: How Do I Know That The Profit Figures That The Sellers Claim Are True?</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div id=\"accordion-6\" class=\"accordion-section-content open\">\r\n<h4>A: As part of the acquisition process, you will have to go through \"due diligence.\" During this period the seller is required to present documents to verify his profit numbers.</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"accordion-4\" class=\"accordion-section-content open\">\r\n<h2>Q: How Much Money Will It Take To Buy A Small Business?</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div id=\"accordion-8\" class=\"accordion-section-content open\">\r\n<h4>A: Businesses vary in price a great deal, however, it would be unlikely that one could buy a business with much less of a down payment than $50,000.</h4>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Buyer FAQS','','inherit','closed','closed','','1088-revision-v1','','','2016-06-22 01:13:41','2016-06-22 01:13:41','',1088,'http://dev.vinehurst.com/2016/06/22/1088-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1093,1,'2016-06-22 01:14:02','2016-06-22 01:14:02','<b>Work With Us and Boost Your Bottom Line.</b>\r\n\r\n<b>Why Partner with Vinehurst?</b>\r\n\r\nVinehurst has been advising business owners since 2003 on how to properly sell their company. With over 750 successful transactions to date, Vinehurst is the industry leader and innovator.\r\n\r\n<b>Utilize our Reputation.</b>\r\n\r\nAt Vinehurst, our word is our bond. We treat all our clients with honesty and respect. Our outstanding reputation reflects that.\r\n\r\n<b>Benefit by our Extensive Marketing Reach.</b>\r\n\r\nAfter 13 years in the business, our database and network of financially qualified business buyers is unrivalled. From angel investors to PEGs, we have access to them, and they trust who we represent. Many of our buyers are repeat clients.\r\n\r\n<b>Take advantage of our expedited selling process.</b>\r\n\r\nAs they said back then, we don\'t \"dilly dally\" when it comes to marketi